title: Russia has spent over $300 million on influencing foreign elections since 2014, US officials say
description: Russia has covertly transferred over $300 million to foreign political parties around the globe since 2014, a senior Biden administration official said Tuesday, citing a review by the US intelligence community.

title: Americans won't be going crazy with holiday gifting this year
description: The kids, the grandparents, the babysitter, maybe your favorite aunt or uncle. That's it.

title: Blinken calls Iran's latest response to nuclear deal proposal a 'step backward'
description: Iran has taken "a step backward" with its latest response to a nuclear deal proposal, US Secretary of State Antony Blinken said Monday, calling a near-term agreement "unlikely."

title: Analysis: The clock is ticking on a big threat to the US economy
description: This Friday, tens of thousands of railroad workers are poised to go on strike, potentially bringing a nearly a third of all US freight to a grinding halt. It would be the first national rail strike in 30 years.
